Get dbnomics

Get dbnomics

get_dbnomics(endpoint, slug, suffix)

Arguments

endpoint
a string either "providers", "datasets" or "series"
slug
a string name of the slug
suffix
a suffix. For instance "values"

Value

a get request

Examples


get_dbnomics(endpoint = "series", slug = "bis-pp-ls-q-au")
#> 200
#> Response [https://api.db.nomics.world/api/v1/json/series/bis-pp-ls-q-au]
#>   Date: 2017-04-07 07:56
#>   Status: 200
#>   Content-Type: application/json
#>   Size: 21.8 kB
#> 


# https://api.db.nomics.world/api/v1/json/datasets/insee-cna-2010-dep-apu/values
get_dbnomics(
endpoint = "datasets",
slug = "insee-cna-2010-dep-apu",
suffix = "values")
#> 200
#> Response [https://api.db.nomics.world/api/v1/json/datasets/insee-cna-2010-dep-apu/values]
#>   Date: 2017-04-07 07:56
#>   Status: 200
#>   Content-Type: application/json
#>   Size: 69.4 kB
#>
